Purpose
This file implements the planner agent as an LLM-backed planning stage.

Linear intent
1. Open `Lwt.Infix` so the asynchronous result mapping reads naturally.
2. Define a local maximum number of plan steps.
3. Expose the agent id as `Planner`.
4. Keep a small local fallback plan path so the agent can still normalize unusable output.
5. Provide helpers that split raw text, trim numbering prefixes, and normalize multi-line plan output.
6. Provide a local deterministic `plan_from_text` fallback based on text segmentation.
7. Build a planner-specific LLM instruction that asks for short execution steps with no extra commentary.
8. Convert the LLM usage information into the framework metrics and notes format.
9. In `run`, accept only `Text` payloads.
10. Read the planner profile from the runtime services configuration.
11. Call `Llm_bulkhead_client.invoke_chat` so the planner goes through BulkheadLM and the configured provider route.
12. Parse the LLM text into normalized `Stage N: ...` lines.
13. Fall back to the local planning heuristic if the model returns no usable lines.
14. Return a typed `Plan` payload plus metrics and notes.
15. Reject unsupported payload kinds with a typed error payload.

